1. The Russian Central Bank proposed a three-year crypto trading pilot, which is limited to investors holding $11.5 million in assets or $50 million in annual income;
2. Hyperliquid 50x leverage whale switched to GMX, opened a $45.17 million ETH short order, and the liquidation price was $1,982;
3. The Ethermine-related wallet, which had been silent for three years, withdrew 2,692 ETH from OKX, about $5.01 million;
4. Deribit: About $3.27 billion in crypto options will expire this Friday, and the biggest pain point for BTC is $86,000;
5. Zhu Su: The rise of CeDeFi is the most bearish for ETH, and Ethereum needs to embrace truly decentralized applications;
6. Trader Eugene: Market views need to be adjusted flexibly, and excessive bearishness may be the biggest mistake;
7. "Band whales" recently failed in high-frequency trading, and their $67.18 million BTC and ETH positions had a floating loss of $2.74 million;
8. Trader Eugene: Bitcoin still has room to fall, or it may test the key psychological level of $66,000;
9. Financial disclosures show that six members of Trump's cabinet hold Bitcoin assets;
10. Nebraska implements new regulations requiring cryptocurrency ATMs to provide anti-fraud warnings;
11. Babylon Foundation: Airdrop registration deadline extended to March 19;
12. DeFiance Capital CEO: The speculation bubble of crypto infrastructure has burst, and application valuations are more attractive;
13. The Hong Kong Securities Regulatory Commission responded to the fake Binance SMS scam: no hesitation to take action on any violations, but no comment on individual cases;
14. Hyperliquid AUM had a net outflow of US$166 million in a single day, the second largest in history;
15. Bybit CEO: The 50x leveraged whale ETH long order liquidation event on Hyperliquid may promote innovation in CEX and DEX liquidation mechanisms;
16. Turkey has introduced new regulations to strengthen cryptocurrency supervision, covering exchanges, custody and wallet services;
17. Hyperliquid 50x leverage whale opened orders on two platforms, with a total position size of nearly 70 million US dollars;
18. Barclays: The Federal Reserve is expected to cut interest rates by 25 basis points in June and September respectively.
